# Example environment file — copy to `backend/.env` and edit. Everything here is optional;
# the canonical defaults live in the code. A value set here PINS it (overrides the default).

# --- API server ---
# Comma-separated origins allowed by CORS. Only matters when the frontend calls the API
# directly (not through the Vite dev proxy). Serving the built UI same-origin
# (`make start` / `make host`) does not exercise CORS at all.
#APP_CORS_ORIGINS=http://localhost:5173,http://127.0.0.1:5173

# Path to the built frontend served as static files by the single-server modes.
# Defaults to ../frontend/dist (produced by `make build`).
#APP_STATIC_DIR=../frontend/dist

# --- LAN hosting (`make host`) ---
# `make host` serves the API + built UI to every device on your Wi-Fi. HOST and PORT are read
# by the launcher from the *shell/Make* environment (not from this .env file), e.g.
#   make host PORT=9000     or     HOST=127.0.0.1 make host
#   HOST  bind address. Default 0.0.0.0 (all interfaces = reachable on the LAN).
#         Set 127.0.0.1 to keep it on this machine only.
#   PORT  base port (default 8000); the launcher auto-advances if it's busy.
#
# SECURITY: 0.0.0.0 exposes the app to everyone on the network. This app has NO
# authentication, and its tools move and permanently delete files on this Mac — run
# `make host` only on a Wi-Fi you trust.

# --- Magnet Scraper (Automatic mode) ---
# Base URL of the site to walk, and the "last watched" video URL used as the stopping anchor.
# CUTOFF_VIDEO is advanced automatically to the newest link after each successful run.
#WEBSITE_URL=https://example.com
#CUTOFF_VIDEO=https://example.com/last-watched-video

# --- Optimized-IP Subscription ---
# SQLite database path (default: backend/data/sub.db).
#SUB_DB_PATH=
# Require ?token=… on subscription links.
#SUB_ACCESS_TOKEN=
# Host used in subscription links; defaults to this Mac's .local name, then a LAN IP.
#SUB_PUBLIC_HOST=
